        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 1 at 7:12PM CDT until July 1 at 7:45PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 712 PM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from near Beans Crossroads to near Troy Municipal Airport
to near Glenwood, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Troy, Goshen, Banks, Antioch, Linwood, Ansley, Troy Municipal
Airport, Troy University, Orion, Springhill, China Grove, Sandfield,
Mossy Grove, and Henderson.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
